	(252,3,'2022-06-08 11:12:29','2022-06-08 10:12:29','<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h3>INTRODUCTION</h3>\r\n<p>We are committed to protecting the privacy and security of your personal information.</p>\r\n<p>This website is designed to comply with the EU General Data Protection Regulation 2018 (GDPR) legislation. Under the terms of GDPR for the purposes of general sales and marketing, Church Barn Group is the Data Controller, and decides why and how your personal information is processed.</p>\r\n<p>This policy explains what we collect, how and why we collect and how it is protected.</p>\r\n<p>We may change the policy from time to time so please revisit this page to ensure youre still happy.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>WHAT WE COLLECT</h3>\r\n<p><strong>The information you provide voluntarily</strong></p>\r\n<p>When you use our online forms, we will collect your name, email address, phone number and enquiry details. We will process your enquiry by sending it via an encrypted email over the internet. We store your enquiry in our systems whilst we process it. We only store your information whilst it is required. If you opt in to receive further marketing information from us then your information is retained until you opt out of this service. You can unsubscribe from our emails at anytime.</p>\r\n<p><strong>The information we automatically collect</strong></p>\r\n<p>When you browse our website or interact with an email that we send to you, we may collect information about your browsing activities.</p>\r\n<p>This website uses Google Analytics (GA) to track user interaction. This enables us to analyse how many users we have visiting our website. Google is a third party data processor which means they process data on our behalf. They capture information relating to your visit, for example how many pages you viewed and how long your stayed on the website. They do not capture any information that means you or your visit can be identified. GA places cookies on your computer to track this information.</p>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>HOW WE LOOK AFTER YOUR DATA</h3>\r\n<p>We will only use your information for the purpose specified, and will never sell, rent, distribute or make public the information you provide us. We follow best practice to ensure that your data remains secure.</p>\r\n<p>We will inform all relevant parties and authorities within 48hours, should there by any unlawful breach of data our security that results in any identifiable personal data being stolen.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>WHERE WE STORE/PROCESS YOUR DATA</h3>\r\n<p>This website is hosted by Siteground within a UK data centre. All facilities are well protected by 247 human security, biometrics, access control man traps, bullet proof lobbies and video surveillance.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>DATA CONTROLLER</h3>\r\n<p>The data controller of this website is Church Barn Group whose registered office is:Church House, The Street, Washington,West Sussex RH20 4AS.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Privacy Policy','','inherit','closed','closed','','3-revision-v1','','','2022-06-08 11:12:29','2022-06-08 10:12:29','',3,'https://churchbarn.nsmpreview.com/?p=252',0,'revision','',0),
